Sentencas: Ba0.5Sr0.5Co1-xFexO3-delta (x = 0.2, 0.6, and 0.8) and Ba0.5Sr0.5Cu1-xFexO3-delta (x = 0.6 and 0.8) perovskite oxides have been investigated as cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5M1-xFexO3-δ (M=Co and Cu) perovskite oxide cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: All the samples synthesized by a citrate EDTA complexing method were single-phase cubic perovskite solid solutions.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5M1-xFexO3-δ (M=Co and Cu) perovskite oxide cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: Then, the thermal expansion coefficient, electrical conductivities, the oxygen vacancy concentrations, the polarization resistances (R-p), and the power densities were measured.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5M1-xFexO3-δ (M=Co and Cu) perovskite oxide cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: An increase in the Co content resulted in a decrease in the polarization resistance, the electrical conductivities at low temperatures, and the inflection point of the thermal expansion coefficient, but it led to an increase in the electrical conductivities at high temperatures, the oxygen vacancy concentrations, and the maximum power densities.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5M1-xFexO3-δ (M=Co and Cu) perovskite oxide cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The Cu-based system has similar behavior to the Co-based system; yet, in terms of the electrical conductivities, high Cu content gave a better result than low content for the entire range of temperatures.
Titulo: Characterization of Ba0.5Sr0.5M1-xFexO3-δ (M=Co and Cu) perovskite oxide cathode materials for intermediate temperature solid oxide fuel cells
